# Project Defaults

These are [P2] defaults. Existing repository evidence overrides them. Do not migrate stack, database, UI framework, package manager, or tooling unless the user asks.

## Reliability

- Handle, propagate, or convert errors explicitly. Do not silently discard fallible results.
- Libraries return errors instead of exiting the process.
- Avoid crash-only handling in production paths unless the invariant is proven and local convention supports it.

## Security and Data

- Validate external input at trust boundaries.
- Use parameterized database queries.
- Prefer platform secret stores or environment-provided secrets. Never hardcode credentials.
- Prefer PostgreSQL for new persistent datastores in this project family, but preserve existing datastore choices.

## Frontend and Node

- Prefer Rust Leptos or Python Reflex for new UI in this project family.
- Preserve existing web stacks when the repo already uses React, Vue, Svelte, raw web assets, Node services, or another framework.
- Node is acceptable for tooling and for repos that already use Node as product code.

## Scripts

- Keep durable automation in repo scripts when it improves reproducibility.
- Keep one-off investigation scripts out of the repo unless the user asks to preserve them as tooling, runbooks, tests, or release automation.

## Maintainability

- Prefer named constants for meaningful magic values.
- Comments explain why, not what.
- Avoid broad refactors unless required by the request or needed to make the fix safe.
